SPECTRA v1.0.0 — Two-Tier Licensing
====================================

The SPECTRA release_package/ contains components released under two distinct
licensing tiers. Reusers must respect both.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Tier 1: SPECTRA-authored components — Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
        International (CC-BY 4.0)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Scope: the SPECTRA OWL ontology, SHACL shapes, PyLODE HTML documentation,
SpectraCQ v1.0 (137 CQs and English question text), Cypher/SPARQL queries,
synthetic and metadata-only examples, validation scripts and tests
(verify_release.py and reproduce_structural_metrics.py), the cross-WG
metadata-only process KG (examples/process_kg/), the sanitized parsing
pipeline source (pipeline/), and SPECTRA-authored README/ARTIFACT/CHANGELOG.

These components are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0
International License (CC-BY 4.0).

You are free to:
  - Share — copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format
  - Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose,
            even commercially.

Under the following terms:
  - Attribution — You must give appropriate credit, provide a link to the
                  license, and indicate if changes were made. You may do so
                  in any reasonable manner, but not in any way that suggests
                  the licensor endorses you or your use.

Full legal code: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
Summary: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Tier 2: 3GPP-derived text-bearing components — 3GPP attribution under
        applicable ETSI/3GPP terms (NOT relicensed as SPECTRA-authored)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Scope: the per-WG body-text knowledge graphs (kg/per_wg/) in so far as
they contain sentence-level rendered text extracted from 3GPP Technical
Documents, Change Requests, Liaison Statements, Technical Specifications,
and Technical Reports. Original 3GPP documents are publicly available at
https://www.3gpp.org/ftp/.

The text literals in these components are 3GPP-derived content and are
NOT relicensed under CC-BY 4.0 by the SPECTRA authors. They are
redistributed with explicit 3GPP attribution under the applicable
ETSI/3GPP redistribution terms, mirroring the attribution style used by
prior 3GPP-text resources such as TSpec-LLM (Nikbakht et al., 2024) and
the GSMA telecom-kg-rel19 release. Reusers of these components must
preserve 3GPP attribution and comply with applicable ETSI/3GPP terms in
addition to any further use rights granted by SPECTRA.

The SPECTRA authors disclaim any claim of authorship over the original
3GPP text content; only the schema, structure, and parsing/encoding work
that materializes 3GPP text into RDF are SPECTRA-authored and fall under
Tier 1.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Out of scope (not bundled in this release)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Raw Neo4j instance dumps and VectorDB embeddings are not bundled in this
release because of size constraints; they are regenerable from the
released kg/per_wg/ and pipeline/ components.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
Contact and corrections
----------------------------------------------------------------------

For licensing questions, attribution corrections, or rights clarifications,
file an issue at https://github.com/spectra-ontology/spec-trace/issues.
